[zero_shot][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 25/100 done id=gsm8k_test_326 prediction="Let's break it down step-by-step:\n\n1. Initially, some people got on the bus at the terminal.\n2. At the first bus stop, 5 more people got in.\n3. At the second bus stop, 7 people got down and 8 more got in.\n\nTo find out how many people got on the bus at the terminal, we need to consider the net change in the number of passengers from the first two stops.\n\n- From the first stop: +5 (people got in)\n- From the second stop: -7 (people got down) + 8 (people got in)\n\nNet change = Initial passengers + People added - People removed\n\nSo, the net change is:\n+5 - 7 + 8 = 6\n\nThis means that 6 people got off the bus at the first stop and then 6 people got on the bus at the second stop.\n\nNow, if there were a total of 20 people heading to the third stop, and we know that 6 people got on the bus at the first stop and 6 people got on the bus at the second stop, then the remaining 20 - 6 - 6 = 10 people must have gotten on the bus at the terminal." gold='14' correct=False
