[zero_shot][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][csqa] sample 42/100 done id=055817d8d703d3c2802545e3fccdcde3 prediction="To determine what humans do to other humans after death, let's consider each option:\n\nA. Celebrate - This is not something that happens after death; it's an activity done before death.\n\nB. Burial - After death, bodies are typically buried or cremated according to cultural practices. This is a common method of disposing of human remains.\n\nC. Life - While some people believe in reincarnation, which involves rebirth, this is not a standard practice for most cultures.\n\nD. Rebirth - This is a belief system that suggests that souls can return to the body at some point after death. However, this is not a physical act but rather a spiritual concept.\n\nE. Decomposition - This process occurs naturally when organic matter decomposes over time. It doesn't happen after death.\n\nBased on this analysis, the correct answer is B. burial. Humans are typically buried or cremated after death, as these are common methods of disposing of human remains." gold='B' correct=False
