[zero_shot][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][mmlu] sample 6/100 done id=mmlu_test_711 prediction='To provide accurate and detailed answers, I will analyze each option carefully:\n\nA. "They may have difficulty reading the screen."\n- This statement is partially true but oversimplifies the issue. While some older adults might struggle with reading screens due to age-related vision issues or other factors, it\'s not universally true. Many older adults can still read well on computers and smartphones.\n\nB. "Less than 30% of people over 65 years have access to the internet."\n- This statement is incorrect because it directly contradicts the claim made in the question. If less than 30% of people over 65 have access to the internet, then they would indeed need internet-based information sources.\n\nC. "The internet is aimed at younger people."\n- This statement is false. Internet usage has been increasing among all ages, including those over 65. It\'s more common for older adults to use the internet through mobile devices like smartphones rather than traditional desktop computers.\n\nD. "They may not be able to type."\n- This statement is also incorrect. Older adults often have trouble with typing due to age-related changes in their motor skills and cognitive abilities. However, it\'s important to note that many older adults can still type if they\'re using assistive' gold='B' correct=False
