[zero_shot][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][mmlu] sample 8/100 done id=mmlu_test_1139 prediction="Let's analyze each statement one by one:\n\nI. The trace of \\( A^2 \\) is nonnegative.\n- This statement is true because the trace of a matrix is the sum of its diagonal elements. For \\( A^2 \\), since \\( A \\) is an \\( n \\times n \\) matrix, \\( A^2 \\) will also have \\( n \\) diagonal elements (one from each row). Therefore, the sum of these \\( n \\) diagonal elements is always nonnegative.\n\nII. If \\( A^2 = A \\), then the trace of \\( A \\) is nonnegative.\n- This statement is false. If \\( A^2 = A \\), it means that \\( A \\) is an idempotent matrix (i.e., \\( A^2 = A \\)). However, the trace of an idempotent matrix can be zero or negative depending on the specific matrix. Without additional information about the properties of \\( A \\), we cannot definitively say whether the trace of \\( A \\) is nonnegative or not.\n\nIII. The trace of \\( AB \\) is the product of the traces of \\( A \\) and \\( B \\).\n- This statement is true. The trace of the product of two" gold='A' correct=False
