[zero_shot][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][mmlu] sample 9/100 done id=mmlu_test_1169 prediction='To solve this problem, we need to analyze the given determinant equation and determine which statements about the matrix \\( A \\) are true.\n\nGiven:\n\\[ \\det(A - \\lambda I) = -\\lambda^3 + 3\\lambda^2 + \\lambda - 3 \\]\n\n### Step-by-Step Analysis:\n\n#### Statement I: The trace of \\( A \\) is 3.\nThe trace of a matrix is the sum of its diagonal elements. For matrix \\( A \\), the trace is simply the sum of all its diagonal entries (which are the eigenvalues).\n\nFrom the given determinant equation, we can see that the coefficient of \\(\\lambda\\) in the polynomial \\(-\\lambda^3 + 3\\lambda^2 + \\lambda - 3\\) is \\(-1\\). This means that the leading term of the polynomial is \\(-\\lambda^3\\), indicating that the trace of \\( A \\) is indeed 3.\n\nTherefore, statement I is true.\n\n#### Statement II: The determinate of \\( A \\) is -3.\nThe determinant of a matrix is equal to the product of its eigenvalues. From the given determinant equation, we know that the constant term (-3) corresponds to the value of the determinant' gold='D' correct=False
