[zero_shot][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][mmlu] sample 21/100 done id=mmlu_test_2286 prediction="Let's solve this step-by-step:\n\n1. **Total Time Spent**: Keri spent a total of 3 hours on her homework.\n\n2. **Time Spent on Science**: We know that Keri spent half an hour (1/2 hour) on science.\n\n3. **Calculate Remaining Time**: To find out how much time was spent on other subjects, we subtract the time spent on science from the total time:\n   \\[\n   \\text{Remaining Time} = 3\\ \\text{hours} - 0.5\\ \\text{hours} = 2.5\\ \\text{hours}\n   \\]\n\n4. **Time Spent on Other Subjects**: Since Keri spent the same amount of time on all subjects, we divide the remaining time by 2 to find out how much time was spent on each subject:\n   \\[\n   \\text{Time per Subject} = \\frac{2.5\\ \\text{hours}}{2} = 1.25\\ \\text{hours}\n   \\]\n\n5. **Number of Subjects**: Now, we need to determine how many subjects were studied if each subject took 1.25 hours. We do this by dividing the total time spent on other" gold='C' correct=False
