[zero_shot][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][mmlu] sample 22/100 done id=mmlu_test_2547 prediction='To construct a truth table for the given argument, we need to evaluate each of its components:\n\n1. **I ≡ ~J**: This means that I is logically equivalent to the negation of J.\n2. **I ∨ J / I**: This part checks if either I or J is true.\n\nLet\'s fill out the truth table:\n\n| I | ~J | I ∨ J | I ≡ ~J |\n|---|-----|--------|---------|\n| T  | F   | T     | F       |\n| T  | F   | T     | F       |\n| F  | T   | T     | T       |\n| F  | T   | T     | T       |\n\nNow let\'s analyze the truth values of the statement "I ≡ ~J" based on the truth table:\n\n- When I = T and J = F, then I ≡ ~J = T (since I is true).\n- When I = F and J = T, then I ≡ ~J = F (since I is false).\n\nSince the statement "I ≡ ~J" can only be true under specific conditions (either both I and J are true or both I and J are false), it cannot be' gold='D' correct=False
