[zero_shot][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][mmlu] sample 76/100 done id=mmlu_test_10617 prediction="To solve this problem, we'll use the Capital Asset Pricing Model (CAPM), which states that the required return on an asset can be calculated using the formula:\n\n\\[ \\text{Required Return} = R_f + \\beta \\times (\\text{Expected Return on Market} - R_f) \\]\n\nWhere:\n- \\( R_f \\) is the risk-free rate,\n- \\( \\beta \\) is the beta of the stock,\n- Expected Return on Market is given as 10%.\n\nLet's calculate the required returns for both companies.\n\n### For Plaid Pants' Common Stock:\n1. **Beta**: 0.90\n2. **Risk-Free Rate**: 6%\n3. **Expected Return on Market**: 10%\n\nPlugging these values into the CAPM formula:\n\n\\[ \\text{Required Return}_{\\text{Plaid}} = 6\\% + 0.90 \\times (10\\% - 6\\%) \\]\n\\[ \\text{Required Return}_{\\text{Plaid}} = 6\\% + 0.90 \\times 4\\% \\]\n\\[ \\text{Required Return}_{\\text{Plaid}} = 6\\% + 3.6" gold='B' correct=False
